Discovered this new place in the town. Kabab is fresh and juicy, lamb is amazing. Portions are perfectly sized - not too small not too big. The only cons i could think of it’s relatively small place.
Excellent food and atmosphere. I really like their chicken & lamb kebob combo.

Was bummed that they didn’t have vegetarian Bolani. However, the food we ordered was tasty. Bread served was cold. The sauces were tasty. Complimentary salad was fine, dough drink was yum. Kids loved Salmon And chicken kebab. Would come back here and recommend to try at least one time if not more.
Really good food... they get very good quality meats, and they cook it just right - very flavorful. Their flavored rice and Afghan bread are also delicious!
